# 🏥 Health Insurance Cost Predictor

An end-to-end Machine Learning project that predicts health insurance charges based on user details such as age, BMI, smoking status, and more.

The project includes:
- Data Analysis
- Feature Engineering
- Model Training
- Model Evaluation
- Web Deployment using Streamlit
- AWS EC2 Hosting

---

## 🎯 Problem Statement

Predict the medical insurance cost of an individual using demographic and lifestyle information.

---

## 📊 Dataset Features

- age → Age of the person  
- gender → Male / Female  
- bmi → Body Mass Index  
- children → Number of dependents  
- smoker → Smoking status (yes/no)  
- region → Residential area  
- charges → Insurance cost (target)

---

## ⚙️ Workflow

### 1. Data Analysis
- Checked distributions and relationships
- Found smoking and BMI strongly impact charges

### 2. Preprocessing
- Label encoding for categorical data
- Feature scaling using StandardScaler

### 3. Model Training
Models tested:
- Linear Regression
- Random Forest
- XGBoost (Best Model)

### 4. Evaluation
- R² Score: ~0.80  
- Error metrics (MAE, RMSE)

---

## 🚀 Deployment

### Streamlit App
Interactive UI where users input details and get predictions instantly.

```bash
streamlit run app.py

